Balsamic Vinegar Pork with Couscous Salad You need: 1 package of pork cutlets 1 chili pepper (I used fresh Chilis, but you could probably use chili powder) approx. 1 cup of Balsamic vinegar (till it fills up a bowl, atleast) Olive Oil (use as directed)

1 box of instant couscous (no fancy shit. Just get the box and make the serving) 1 box of cherry tomatos or 3 medium sized tomatos 1 can of chick peas (garbonzo beans) 1 can of black olives, sliced 1 small red onion

Directions

1. If you havent already defrosted the pork, do that. Dice the onions and cut the cherry tomatos in half (or dice the regular tomatos). 2. Turn the stove on and coat the pan in olive oil. Put the onions and tomatos in the pan and let cook till brown. On another burner, start the couscous as directed on the box. 3. When the onions and tomatos are done, mix them in with the couscous. Add the chick peas and olives and mix it all together. 4. Mix the chili powder/chilis with the balsamic vinegar. Coat the pork in it, making sure every part gets coated. Pan-fry it till done. You should be done :D If you have any questions, just comment Sorry, no pictures. We ate it too fast!
